Dutch filmmaker Theo van Gogh, who had received threats over a controversial film he made about Islam, was shot and stabbed to death Tuesday while cycling on an Amsterdam street, officials said. van Gogh was known for his outspoken criticism of Islam He was killed Tuesday morning while on his way to work in Amsterdam. After the film was shown on Dutch television in August, Van Gogh received death threats and police stepped up measures to protect him, much against his will.